flowRoot.flowPara: Shown when the device is woken up and is locked. Switches to the authentication state with a click, tap or key press.
Authentication is shown on key press, click or tap. This state is also shown by default for login (as opposed to unlock).
The session selection menu is shown in the bottom-right, and the OS logo is shown.
∙ A summary of notifications that have been received while the device has been locked.
∙ Media controls for music/video, when it's playing.
∙ Icons to indicate when cmart card and fingerprint authentication is available.
∙ A back button, which navigates to the user selection screen.
Esc returns to the presentation state, if that was previously shown.
Includes:
Messages that are required to be shown on login. Admins could change the text of the button, depending on their reuirements.
When notifications arrive and the screen is locked, the app icon and name are shown on a black screen. This behavior should be configurable, and should probably be off by default.

Incorrect password message. There shouldn't be any delay between an incorrect attempt and being able to retry. However, after three attempts input should be insensitive for 5 seconds and the message should read "Three incorrect attempts. Please wait to try again."
